    • Field Detail

      • UNUSED_COMMAND_POLICY

        public final ModuleOption<UnusedCommandPolicy> UNUSED_COMMAND_POLICY
        Describes how Commodore should handle commands that perform no actions, such as the first of two consecutive scoreboard players set commands on the same entity. Possible values are:
        1. UnusedCommandPolicy.KEEP: The unused commands will remain in the function.
        2. UnusedCommandPolicy.COMMENT_OUT: The unused command will not run, but will remain as a function comment.
        3. UnusedCommandPolicy.REMOVE: The unused command will not be added to the function.
        Default value is UnusedCommandPolicy.REMOVE.

      • EXPORT_ACCESS_LOGS

        public final ModuleOption<java.lang.Boolean> EXPORT_ACCESS_LOGS
        Describes whether scoreboard access logs should be exported. This is a debug feature used to evaluate how each command reports its scoreboard accesses. If set to true, upon compiling the module, *.accesslog files will be created alongside functions, detailing each scoreboard access for each command and its resolution (whether it was used or unused).
